title: I Came Here To Win! | Paikidze vs Wang | US Championship 2018. | Armageddon
description:
#agadmator Check out Annie Wang winning over 200 points in a single tournament https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qViSW8R-mmE&t=15s

Check out the full article on this event https://www.chess.com/news/view/paikidze-takes-u-s-womens-championship-in-armageddon

The 2018 U.S. Women's Championship is a 12-player round-robin featuring the strongest female players in the USA, who compete for USD $100,000 in prize money and the title of 2018 U.S. Women's Champion. If two or more players tie for first place a playoff will be held.

For the 10th consecutive year the Saint Louis Chess Club is hosting the event. Players receive 90 minutes for the first 40 moves followed by 30 minutes for the rest of the game, with a 30-second increment from move one. Draw offers are not allowed before move 30. Official website: uschesschamps.com

Nazi Paikidze vs Annie Wang
US Women Championship (2018), Armageddon, Apr-30 
Caro-Kann Defense: Exchange. Rubinstein Variation (A08)

1. Nf3 e6 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 d5 4. O-O Be7 5. d3 c5 6. Nbd2 Nc6 7. e4 b6 8. e5 Nd7 9. Re1 Qc7 10. Qe2 Bb7 11. c4 d4 12. Nf1 h6 13. h4 O-O-O 14. N1h2 g5 15. h5 Rdf8 16. Ng4 Kb8 17.
